post_text:
Here is the updated risk gauge from the Four Corners Health department as of today. We are still in yellow. In order for us to determine our own risk level, we also look at our own school numbers as well as the guidance from Four Corners Health. We are moving in the right direction, and we will continue to implement our plans for the yellow risk category. If things were to change, we will let everyone know.

As a reminder, please be making sure that your child comes to school with a different mask each day. Make sure that you are washing them regularly to prevent other illnesses from being contracted.

Thank you for another great week!

#EvenBetter
Mr. Eldridge

Alright, folks - here is the updated risk dial from Four Corners Health Department. As you see, our health district is right on the line between yellow and orange. We will continue to operate in yellow for the time being. If things were to change, we will let everyone know.

Keep in mind the following will be the changes IF we move into orange:
- Face Coverings will be worn 100% of the time.
- Students MAY eat lunch in their classrooms.
- Visitors to the school will be by appointment only.
- All community members attending events in the buildings will be required to wear a face-covering 100% of the time.

Mr. Eldridge

post_text:
THANK YOU Stop Inn and Dan/Jan Sypal!!
Dan and Jan donated $500 to our East Butler FCCLA Chapter. Their annual Fireworks Stand was a success and they wanted to share some of the proceeds with a Youth Organization in Butler County. Our FCCLA Chapter applied and was chosen!

The East Butler FCCLA chapter's annual activities include: Pink Out Fundraisers (Relay for Life Donation), hosting 2 school dances, adopting a needy family at Christmastime, working concession stands, school wide contribution drive, attending leadership and public speaking events, attending and competing at the State FCCLA Conference, parties/social events among the chapter members, and simply Having Fun.

FCCLA is a Family Focused Student organization!!
Thanks Stop Inn for making our day at East Butler #EvenBetter!!

McCool Junction Volleyball Guidelines
All fans will come through the North Gym Doors.
Visiting fans will sit on the North Side of the gym.
Home fans will sit on the South Side of the gym.
Social Distancing will be encouraged when getting concessions and using restrooms. McCool Fans will be encouraged to use cafeteria restroom ‚Äì visiting fans will use gym restrooms.
All concession food will be individually wrapped ‚Äì which could limit offerings. Servers at the concession stand will be required to wear mask and gloves.
All home games will be telecast on Striv so fans can watch from home.
Fans will be encouraged to wear mask in the gym.
No Pep Band will be permitted to play or cheerleaders from home or visiting teams.
50% Capacity - which will allow us to have 200 people in attendance.

post_text:
Class of 2020,

We are so proud of everything that you have accomplished. I felt that it is only fitting that as we enter what was suppose to be your graduation weekend, that we honor and recognize you. Did you know that the class of 2020 is a historical class? Here are some interesting facts - the iPhone is older than all of you, you were 3 years old when YouTube was created, you were 2 years old when Facebook launched, 4 years old when Twitter launched, and texting is older than you as well as the college graduates as it was created in 1992. Now you end your high school career in the midst of a pandemic. You have certainly experienced a lot!! I know that I can speak for everyone at East Butler Public schools, that we wish you nothing but the best, and we cannot wait to see what the future holds for each and every one of you.

Stay Safe & Healthy!

Mr. Eldridge #EvenBetter

post_text:
A phone call is scheduled for tonight with this information as well.
Three announcements-
1) Easter Break has been extended to include Monday. There will be no online classes on both this coming Friday and Monday.
2) Our last day of school has been moved up to May 13. After May 13 online classes will end and summer break will begin. We are developing our plan for check in of the resources we sent home with you for online learning.
3) Students, please continue to do your best to complete the work our teachers assign. Every task is designed to help you be prepared for next school year. We know this a difficult time but we need your best effort on the assigned activities.

Educational programming for elementary students will air from 9 a.m. to 11 a.m. CST and for secondary students from 1 p.m. to 3 p.m. CST, Monday through Friday. Families can live stream NCN on the website, download the NCN app on any mobile device, or access the programming through a local cable provider, and stream on Amazon Fire, Apple TV, and Roku apps. March 30 at 2:28 PM ¬∑

Four Corners District Confirms its First Case of Travel-Related COVID-19

As of Monday, March 30, 2020, Four Corners Health Department has confirmed its first case of COVID-19. A man in his 50‚Äôs in York County has tested positive for the virus. This case has been determined by Four Corners to be travel-related.

He has minor symptoms and is currently self-isolating at home. He has had very minimal contact with others, and is considered a low-risk to the community.

To help prevent the spread of COVID-19, everyone should do the following:
‚Ä¢ Wash your hands often
‚Ä¢ Avoid close contact
‚Ä¢ Stay home if sick
‚Ä¢ Cover coughs and sneezes
‚Ä¢ Clean and disinfect
‚Ä¢ Avoid touching your eyes, nose and mouth

As a reminder, Directed Health Measures have been issued for Butler, Polk, Seward and York Counties through May 6, 2020. For a copy of the Directed Health Measures, visit www.fourcorners.ne.gov. For questions, please contact the Four Corners Health Department at 402-362-2621.

post_text: #EvenBetter Update on where we are and where we are headed.
text: #EvenBetter Update on where we are and where we are headed.

post_text:
A call is scheduled for 6:00 PM tonight with this information.

On the advice of NDE, East Butler will be closed starting Wednesday, March 18. WE WILL HAVE SCHOOL ON TUESDAY. This closure will last from 6 to 8 weeks, with reevaluations every two weeks to consider reopening. We do not have any cases of COVID 19 infection in this district. NDE is advising this as a preventative measure.

Our timeline for this week-

Tuesday-
We will have school. We will send students home with relevant materials and resources for use at home.

Wednesday-
No students report. No staff reports. East Butler will be completely shut down.

Thursday-
Office staff, administration, and teachers report. The day will be devoted to identifying our priorities and planning delivery of services. We will be in contact with parents and students shortly to convey plans.

Due to recent school closings there is an elevated level of concern around Coronavirus infection. We are continuing to communicate with the Nebraska Department of Education and our local heath agencies as well as monitoring information from the CDC. We have no confirmed cases of infection in our district nor do we have any reason to believe we have come in contact with the Coronavirus. At this time and in our present circumstance these are the most important things you can do:
1) Wash your hands. Do so frequently and be thorough.
2) Cover up when you cough or sneeze.
3) If you are sick, stay home and contact your physician.

post_text:
East Butler Public School District
is accepting applications for the following position for the 2020-2021 School Year:

7-12 Language Arts Teacher

Additional coaching opportunities are available, including Junior High Head Girls Basketball and High School Speech Coach. Willingness to coach or be an activity sponsor is preferred. East Butler is a D1 district with outstanding facilities, staff, 1:1 Laptop technology, and educational resources in a supportive community. Tuition reimbursement is available for advanced degree completion. We are located less than 45 minutes from Lincoln and less than an hour from Omaha. Send a letter of application, resume, references, college credentials, and a copy of your current teaching certificate to the following:

Michael Eldridge, High School Principal
East Butler Public Schools
P.O. Box 36
Brainard, NE 68626
